abstract = {The article introduces the characteristics of flight testing, system engineering, and system-of-systems engineering. It provides a dialectical analysis of the relationships between systems, system-of-systems(SoS), modeling methods, modeling languages, and object-oriented concepts. The complexity of flight test system-of-systems engineering is analyzed in depth. Based on the complexity and development trends of flight test system-of-systems engineering, it explores a model-based, object-oriented approach to aircraft flight test system-of-systems engineering construction. The article conducts a thorough analysis and argumentation in areas such as system architecture design, object-oriented modeling, data structures, and data management, and combines it with model flight testing for practical validation. Simultaneously, the article analyzes the challenges encountered in the construction of flight test systems/systems-of-systems and provides insights into future directions.},
